0.name: 1Harrington Log
0.text:
uh, we really need to get better voice recorders for this.
uhh anyways, yesterday we have finally concluded construction of the secondary research facillity here.
The equipment will arrive in a few days from now. Then we can offically start studdying on this side of the moon.
Which is splendid because have made a recent discovery...
This weird stuff..
Some sort of fungi perhaps?

I am not entirely sure what this is just yet but it has a.. regenerative ability.. at speeds unlike anything we have seen before.

We discovered this when we used a metal pipe to carefully stab a hole into it.
Anwyays.
I should wrap this up now, I'll record another log once we've got something.

Professor Harrington, over and out.

1.name: 2Harrington Log
1.text:
Well, we found something.

It appears this strange growth is neither a fungi.. nor its own organism.
It's its own new thing.
It is able to remember certain growing patern from a genetic blueprint.
Meaning it's alive!
But seamingly not in the traditional way we precieve living things.
Our entire understanding of life was just flipped upside down.
It is even able to grow these weird.. bulbs resembling eyes.
It is unsure if these eyes serve a purpose.. Well.. They must.. Otherwise it wouldn't be growing them.

We will refer to this as.. Cosmic Growth from now on.
That's all I can say for now.

Professor Harrington, over and out.

2.name: 3Harrington Log
2.text:
These old voice recorders are the worst.. 
Right.. 
We've got word from captain Donahue over at the primary facility. 
They have found.. something.. 
It appears to be something new, something unexplored. 
They think it might be some sort of plant which sounds exciting. 

Here however we've made steady progress. 
As mentioned before, this cosmic growth is able to grow.. eyes wherever it pleases. 
At first we thought it might be some sort of defense mechanism. 
But there's no active predators on Cosmocos from the data we've gathered. 
But then we noticed something strange.. 

One of the eyes growing in our incubators was able to move and look around, illuminating whatever it looked at. 
This place is full of surprises. 
More information soon. 

Professor Harrington, over and out.

3.name: 4Harrington Log
3.text:
It's been a strange past few weeks, we've heard that luitenant commander Cunningham was send back to 61 after going mad. 
I have no idea what that's all about. 
But they've started extracting this.. plant I think it was? 
Anyways. 
Research has been going steady, these illuminating eyes don't seem to have a purpose.. 
well.. 
not a definitive one at least. 
Ever since the Cunningham incident it appears to be more.. agressive almost. 
It's certainly strange. 
I wonder if the- 

*Rumbling*

What is happening? 
Everything is bright outside?? 

*More rumbling*

Woah. 
What's happening.

*Agressive rumbling*

There's a what coming at us?! 

*The sounds of a moon ripping itself apart.*

We have been hit. 
Worse. 
We have been separated from Cosmocos. 
I..
I need to go..
